						               													<description>The goal of this economic game is to get as rich as possible during the 10 rounds that the games last, so that you can afford yourself to buy a private island.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Each player starts with 100 million $ starting capital, a pawn and a personal player board in his color that states the possible actions.&amp;#10;     Each round consists of 5 phases: in phase 1 an event card is revealed, in phase 2 each player choose secretely in which market he is going to be active (this is revealed simultaneously), in phase 3 each player (in turn order) may choose an open card from the center of the board, in phase 4 player can buy in the markets via a  blind bidding mechanism, in phase 5 the player can sell to the markets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after 10 rounds, he who accumulated the most money wins Cr&amp;eacute;sus.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
